Not only did he use the phrase "as in Iraq" several times in the text itself, he even used the name of the Bush Declaration of January 2007 as the name of his own declaration: "New Forward Path" without faltering.
Three years ago, he himself criticized the Bush idea of sending fresh troop contingents to Iraq plagued by the civil war as an “irresponsible and, in its conclusions, catastrophic decision.”
The following months, however, showed that the Bush strategy, based on military recommendations, was the only possible and in this respect very successful one to stop talking about Iraq in the news today.
This did not improve Bush’s reputation, because objectively he left his successor a much more grateful starting position than was expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes that the miracle will repeat itself.
He was once again asked by the military to increase the contingent of troops, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghanistan Operation General Stanley McCristal, who, even in spite of the subordination habits, strongly criticized the faltering shooters in the White House.
He called for 40,000 soldiers to be able to reverse the situation for the better.
The president hesitated for three months, but did not come up with a better idea and so he cheated the general by 10,000 soldiers.
From Europe, he has pressed the pledge for another 5,000, even though he himself originally expected at least 10,000.
Most problematic of the entire Obama strategy is his intention to withdraw troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and complete this process within three years. The entire Obama doctrine leaves behind more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the increase in half will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Even in spite of the fraternal war of recent years, Iraq society is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is marked by the contraindication - no one can be trusted and no agreements are made.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, who are accustomed to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they were formally established correctly, remain only fake buildings behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the confusing circumstances that complicate the Pakistan and Iran influences even more.
The building of a "actable state" which is the minimalist goal of the entire operation is also very unrealistic.
Time horizon of Obama strategy obscured by his volunteerism
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only deteriorated further and is now on the brink of an explosion.
Believing that the little soldiers who broke out in the cries of war about the "early homecoming" can create a miracle here, only a truly romantic soul that cannot be impressed by facts.
From the political point of view, the date set for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsibility, because the Taliban will take this as the indirect confession of the American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that the willingness of Europeans to participate in the fighting in Afghanistan is negligible.
Europe’s politicians cannot and do not want to explain to their voters how the security of Germany or Italy is related to the war in the Hindu Kush mountain foreland.
Another possible factor that can radically influence the situation is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the increased sanctions on Iranians do not work, there is a very serious question for the United States whether the problem cannot be solved with troops.
This question needs to be answered in the period when America is stepping up to Obama for the winning withdrawal from Afghanistan.
However, every solution will also mean a dramatic turn in the Afghan situation.
The only consolation plaster for Barack Obama is the fact that there are still three years left until the presidential election, and so there is still enough time for him to resort to a different strategy if it turns out to be a total failure.
