Michelin pointed out that this campaign is part of their commitment to road safety, which "has far more to it than just designing and manufacturing products that are becoming more and more safe every day" and further reaffirmed that they are also helping to get one step closer to this goal every day with other actions of educational and informative character.
This new campaign to promote the use of helmets on the motorcycle, which runs under the slogan 'To be or not to be', will distribute posters to over 500 motorcycle workshops in a first phase in order to achieve the best possible distribution.
In conclusion, Michelin emphasized that road safety is "a constant concern" of the company, and precisely for the reason that, as a manufacturer of tyres for two-wheeled vehicles, they are always committed to the fact that one of their main goals must be the development of ever safer products.
