New Vehicle Assessment Programs
In these days of storms and accidents, not only the car workshops deserve
Every day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are towed to the workshops, where an appraiser must assess the damages incurred and the cost of the repair.
Not a single accident is the same and calculating the cost of the parts and working hours can be a lengthy and complicated task.
The calculation of the repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including the parts and working hours, can take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest IT tools, it is a matter of minutes.
That’s why almost 100% of reviewers use these types of systems.
The service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs collect the information they receive from the manufacturers in order to process it afterwards and offer it to their customers in the form of a useful program.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all expert opinions are created with their products.
The other two companies competing in the tool market for reviewing and drafting a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data that manufacturers provide is anything but simple.
According to Eduardo Vel<0xC3><0xA1>zquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers are working together, each of them providing the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is increasing, to the point that in the last five years even more versions, variants and motorizations have been launched on the market than in the entire fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car enters the market, the work begins for the companies.
It is a laborious task, because every single one of the thousands of vehicle parts must be catagolized and its price entered.
In addition, an "intelligent" graphic image is created from each model, on which you can "click" on different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much-sold model, the work can be completed in a week if the process proceeds quickly.
If it is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months, and currently Audatex has complete information for 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the fleet of vehicles on the roads, it is over 99%.
In order to carry out documentation work and create databases, Audatex has eight centers worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in certain brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics specialists) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests €90 million annually in the development of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers get the updates every other day.
The development of this enormous flow of information allows companies to use it in different ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but depending on the country, there are also tools for managing scrap parts or for calculating the file or residual value of a car.
The only company that provides information about the value of used cars in Spain through a guide is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer this offer in Spain, but in the United States.
By reviewing the products Audatex offers, you can easily get an overview of the type of support it provides to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, with the star of the products being AudaPlus, a standard solution for assessing accidents for the reviewers.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles as well as light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the painting prices.
This tool is paid depending on the purpose, i.e. for each expert report.
It is most expensive for customers who rarely use it, a maximum of ten times a month, namely 5.75 euros per month.
On the other hand, any insurance company that makes thousands of reports negotiates the price with Audatex.
With other products, such as AudaVIN, you can completely identify a vehicle and the equipment with which it ran off the assembly line, solely by means of the chassis number.
AudaGlass deals with the vehicle windscreens, and AudaSubastas is an open service for the specialist market on the Internet, with which you can offer for vehicles that have been declared total damage.
Your statistical service is very useful in identifying trends, carrying out geodemographic analyses or for obtaining information about the deviations by brand and model.
For example, it can be used to investigate how many models of a particular car brand had to go to the workshop due to breakdowns or how many of them were involved in a serious accident in a given period of time.
